news.title: Flex-space market size expected to touch 126 million sq ft by 2028: Report
news.para: Sectors like IT & ITeS, BFSI, consulting, e-commerce, manufacturing, and new-age startups, along with the continuous influx of global captive centers (GCCs) are driving demand.

news.title: 315Work Avenue aims to double its portfolio in next 18 months
news.para: Manas Mehrotra, founder of the company said: "We are also exploring opportunities to expand our reach by entering mall spaces and opening up shared offices to attract more clients."

news.title: DRA Homes to invest Rs 150 crore to develop commercial space in Chennai
news.para: DRA Homes plans to invest Rs 150 crore into the development of an A-grade office complex. It aims to lease the entire building of 1.1 lakh sq ft to a single client, with a rental rate of Rs. 110 per sq ft per month.

news.title: China pushes banks to speed approvals of new loans to developers: Sources
news.para: Most top domestic banks have so far shied away from significantly bolstering credit exposure to the crisis-hit sector despite repeated nudges from Beijing, dashing hopes of a revival in an industry crucial for the economy.

news.title: No hike in property tax in Bengaluru from April 1
news.para: State govt denies 2024-25 Bengaluru property tax revision. 2016 levy method remains. Police crackdown on fake news. Misinformation debunked. No property tax increase, reassuring residents.

news.title: Adam Neumann bids over $500 million to buy back WeWork: Source
news.para: Adam Neumann, the former CEO of WeWork, along with other investors, was reported to be considering a bid to acquire WeWork from bankruptcy, as per Bloomberg.

news.title: Ethiopia to let foreigners own property: Prime Minister
news.para: Currently foreigners are barred from owning houses in Ethiopia, either residential or commercial buildings, which is seen as a hurdle to ongoing efforts to attract foreign investment to the Horn of Africa country.

news.title: China: Shimao Group lays out restructuring proposal
news.para: Under the proposal, Shimao intends to restructure all of its debt, amounting to around $11.7 billion in offshore notes, bonds and other credit facilities.

news.title: Sweden's SBB to buy back debt at 60% discount
news.para: The buyback will trim the struggling property company's debts, which amounted to some 62 billion Swedish crowns ($5.9 billion) at the end of last year.

news.title: Don't supply power to illegal constructions: Bengaluru development body to BESCOM
news.para: BDA told Bescom that it is planning to expand Shivarama Karanth Layout in 12 villages in Yelahanka taluk and one in Bengaluru North taluk.

news.title: Star Housing Finance inks co-lending partnership with Tata Capital Housing Finance
news.para: Kalpesh Dave, CEO of Star HFL said, "We aim to service 5,000 families in our operational geographies in first phase of 6-8 operational quarters."

news.title: Shree Cement commissions first ready-mix concrete plant in Hyderabad
news.para: Shree Cement had acquired five operational plants of StarCrete LLP in Mumbai earlier this month for a consideration of Rs 33.5 crore. Its combined RMC capacity now stands at 512 cubic meters per hour.

news.title: Promoters must name the projects as per sanctioned maps: UP-RERA
news.para: It was also observed that promoters were using project brand names which were different from the names registered with RERA and this was creating doubts amongst the existing and prospective home buyers.

news.title: Bokaro Steel plans mapping exercise to flush out illegal occupants from residential quarters
news.para: Only last year, the BSL management recorded that nearly 1,300 of its quarters were illegally occupied. However, the PSU estimates that the number of illegally occupied quarters could be well beyond 3,000.

news.title: Submit stability certificate for alterations in Chandigarh housing board homes
news.para: Residents of Sectors 41A, 41D, 45C, 45D, 46, 47C, 39B and 29B have been asked to get the structural stability of their dwelling units assessed from the structural engineers empanelled with the Chandigarh administration for the additions/alterations carried out by them and submit the certificate to the Chandigarh Housing Board at their own cost.

news.title: Real estate investors in Europe turn to lawyers after 'huge' CO₂ shock
news.para: Property owners across the region will need to invest vast sums in renovations to ensure their buildings aren't emitting illegal levels of carbon dioxide or consuming excessive amounts of energy, according to lawyers advising the sector.

news.title: High Court urges swift appointment of Karnataka REAT chairperson
news.para: However, the High Court has directed the State to initiate the process of identifying and appointing a member to fill the ensuing vacancy and also the constitution of the Tribunal without any delay.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso buyers flag concerns over redevelopment
news.para: In a meeting held on Sunday, residents alleged that the agreement is “one-sided in nature”, which they felt did not represent their interests fairly.
